== Pickled Veggies ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @radishes{3}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%oz}, reserving juice.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine radishes, juice from half the lemon, ¼ of the onion, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until veggies are slightly pink, ~{30-45%seconds}.

In a separate small #bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp} with lemon zest. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Pork & Pineapple ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pineapple and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned and caramelized, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; remove from pan. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @ground pork{10%oz} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}. Cook, breaking up into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, caramelized pineapple, and reserved pineapple juice until everything is saucy and combined.

== Assembly ==

While pork cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with pork mixture, lemon crema, and as many pickled veggies (draining first) as you like. Pick @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; tear leaves and sprinkle over tacos. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> We're obsessed with sweet and savory flavor combos for dinner, which is why we have a soft spot for tacos al pastor. The dish traditionally involves pork that's marinated in pineapple juice and spices, then slowly spit-roasted for ultra-tender results. In this riff on the classic, we skip the hours of slow-cooking by swapping out the pork shoulder for ground pork. It's browned with a bounty of Southwest spices, simmered with chunks of pineapple until saucy, and stuffed into warm tortillas with lemon crema and pickled onion and radish. You can have all that in just 30 minutes—taco 'bout a dinner winner!